HEADWORD: Deduplication
<hw>De*du`pli*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>de-</ets> + <ets>duplication</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld>
<def>The division of that which is morphologically one organ into two or
more, as the division of an organ of a plant into a pair or
cluster.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deed</ent>⟦br⟧
